                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/180.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>German Embassy reports authorities Guadalajara levying extraordinary taxes
                    discriminatory as against Germans and other foreigners as compared with
                    Mexicans.</p>
                <p>Department had understood from Carothers that collection this extraordinary tax
                    had been suspended.</p>
                <p>Report facts and if attempt is being made to collect tax discriminatory as
                    against foreigners make urgent protest on this ground.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
